Gon Freeces
Hanoi, Vietnam82 contributions
Beautiful and relaxing
Apr 2022 • Family
I’ve read some articles claiming My Khe beach is among top 10 beaches of the world. I can’t tell for sure but it’s definitely a long stunning beach.
Some sorts of entertainment as known as water sports are also available such as jet-skiing, para sailing, wake boarding, banana boat ride (this one is funny as hell), speed boat for rent…
Perfect landscape. You get to see Son Tra peninsula with big mountains and the Lady Buddha statue on the left side of the beach. Also you will see the big city with tall buildings on the right side.
Written September 24, 2022
Cookie Monster
Colombo, Sri Lanka32 contributions
2.0 of 5 bubbles
If you like cranes and high rises looming over a beach you can't even swim at, this is for you.
Jan 2020
Way too commercial- not any shade to be found other than paid lounge chairs and umbrellas. Lined with huge buildings, a busy road and lots of construction in sight. It's ok if all you want is to look at the waves and go for a walk near the sea, but definitely not a 'relaxing' and natural beach environment. Do not come to Da Nang for the beaches. Better of going to some southern islands or Thailand!
Written January 18, 2020
Andrew K
cork, Ireland3 contributions
Good for walking but no swimming
Dec 2022 • Couples
Nice long beach to walk along. Clean and peaceful in December.
Could not find an area to swim as it was too dangerous with the waves. Red no swimming flags displayed all along the beach. Nice to paddle. A lot of people have been taken out to sea by the waves over the last few years so be careful.
Written December 23, 2022
